<br>
Seems like to the minds of some, everyone can cast SoW, KEI, and Temp/Aego/Virtue.  And you'd think the two daggers would be a dead giveaway.<br>
<br>
People who don't know who the fuck you are, coming up to you like you're their best friend, asking for you to pick the lock in CoM/Chardok or steal any Parchments to help his/her 30-40 something person get their epic piece.  Look, if you want something, just be level and don't act like we've been friends for ages<br>
<br>
Tanks who make it their duty to make sure I have ABSOLUTELY NO WAY of landing a backstab.  Sure, accidents happen.  Some others make a damn religion out pressing mobs against the wall like some sick orgy.  Let me do my job to the best of my ability.<br>
<br>
Others who feel the undying need to cast invis ON A ROGUE.  Well shit my skills ain't enough to get around without being seen?  I ran through Hate without any gear without being seen.  Your spell isn't going to make any similar journey any better.<br>
<br>
And my personal favorite.  Those who root for every fucking thing without saying a word.  Okay, one mob has been pulled, you don't get any agro...yet you need to root it?  Lovely.  Just root the bitch while I try to juggle the distance between out of range and too close too the mob (thank you Sony for your fucked up spacing).  One inch too close and I'm getting hit, one inch too far and I'm out of range.  Really, that root on the single mob isn't going to change the tide in battle. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/Barnes101/ishkur.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enyarexev>EnyareXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#330000>(11/14/03 3:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1136.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Game related Peeve's and annoyance's</span><hr size=1> hehe tabi great rant =)<br>
